a]]<br />(Honorary) |nota=leading African-American intellectual for more than half a century; First Black admitted to [[Johns Hopkins University]]; |ref=<ref name=soa/><ref name=skip24/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://afam.nts.jhu.edu/people/Miller/miller.html |title=Dr. Kelly Miller: Johns Hopkins University's First Black Student |work=The History of African Americans form Johns Hopkins University |publisher=[[Johns Hopkins University]] |accessdate=13 December 2010}}</ref>}} {{mem/f |name=[[James A. Porter]] |chapter=Beta |nota=First [[scholar]] whose book ''Modern Negro Art'' became a standard reference work on Black Art in America |ref=<ref name=hb/><ref name=japorter>{{cite web |url=http://www.artnoir.com/index.porter.html |title=John Amos Porter |publisher=artnoir.com |accessdate=2007-07-19 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070409092821/http://artnoir.com/index.porter.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-04-09}}</ref>}} {{mem/f |name=[[Cornel West]] |chapter=[[Sacramento, California|Zeta Beta Lambda]] |nota=Professor of religion at [[Harvard University|Harvard]] and [[Princeton University|Princeton]] |ref=<ref name=soa/>}} }}
===Rhodes scholars=== The [[Rhodes Scholarship]] is the world's oldest and arguably most prestigious international fellowship. The scholarships have been awarded to applicants annually since 1902 by the Rhodes Trust in Oxford on the basis of academic qualities, as well as those of character. {{mem/fstart |ilist= [[File:Wes Moore credit Amunankhra House Ltd.jpg|100px|thumb|Westley Moore]] |alist= {{mem/f |name=[[Norman Washington Manley]]<!-- Also listed in "Government"--> |chapter=[[Miami, Florida|Beta Beta Lambda]] |nota=1914 Rhodes Scholar; Premier of Jamaica, Founder of [[Jamaica]]'s [[People's National Party]] |ref=<ref name=nwm>{{cite web |url=http://www.munualphas.com/manley.html |title=Faces of Alpha Phi Alpha, Manley |accessdate=2007-06-30}}</ref><ref name=jamobs>{{cite news |last=Burke |first=Michael |date=2004-09-04 |url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/columns/html/20040901T220000-0500_65567_OBS_NORMAN_MANLEY_AND_ALOUN_ASSAMBA.asp |title=Norman Manley and Aloun Assamba |work=Jamaica Observer |accessdate=2007-06-30}}</ref>}} {{mem/f |name=[[Wes Moore|Westley Moore]] |chapter=[[Johns Hopkins University|Sigma Sigma]] |nota=2001 Rhodes Scholar |ref=<ref>{{cite news |date=2001-01-22 |url=http://www.jhu.edu/~gazette/2001/jan2201/22briefs.html |title=Hopkins' Honors Rhodes Scholar |work=The Gazette Online |publisher=Johns Hopkins University |accessdate=2007-06-30}}</ref>}} {{mem/f |name=[[Randal Pinkett]]<!-- Also listed in "Entertainment" --> |chapter=[[Columbia, Maryland|Kappa Phi Lambda]] |nota=1994 Rhodes Scholar; 4th Winner of [[National Broadcasting Corporation|NBC's]] reality show, [[The Apprentice (US Season 4)|The Apprentice]] |ref=<ref name=pinkett>{{cite web |url=http://www.randalpinkett.com/about/affiliations.asp |title=Dr. Randal Pinkett, Affiliations |accessdate=2007-10-12}}</ref><ref name=apprentice>{{cite web |url=http://www.nbc.com/The_Apprentice_4/candidates/bio_randal.shtml |title=The Apprentice |publisher=[[National Broadcasting Company|NBC]] |