ier]] |chapter=Beta |nota=First Black President of the [[American Sociological Association]]; Sociologist on race relations; |ref=<ref name=soa/>}} {{mem/f |name=[[Lloyd L. Gaines]] |chapter=[[Lincoln University of Missouri|Alpha Psi]] |nota=Central figure of one of the most important cases in the [[American Civil Rights Movement (1896-1954)|U.S. civil rights movement]]âSupreme Court case styled [[Missouri ex rel. Gaines v. Canada|Gaines v. Canada]] |ref=<ref name=lloydg>{{cite news |first=Robert W. |last=Tabscott |date=2007-03-03 |url=http://www.stltoday.com/stltoday/news/special/srlinks.nsf/story/D60BC9A524A7CE5C86257292007C2508?OpenDocument |title=In 1938, Lloyd Gaines was poised to become a major figure in the desegregation of America. But then he vanished. |work=Post-Dispatch |publisher=STLtoday.com |accessdate=2007-07-22}}</ref>}} {{mem/f |name=[[Lester Granger]] |chapter=[[Dartmouth College|Theta Zeta]] |nota=3rd Executive Secretary of the [[National Urban League]] |ref=<ref name=promalpha/>}} {{mem/f |name=[[Dick Gregory]] |chapter=[[Southern Illinois University|Beta Eta]] |nota=[[United States presidential election, 1968|1968 Presidential candidate]]; comedian, social activist, writer |ref=<ref name=promalpha/><ref name=dickg>{{cite web |url=http://www.africanamericans.com/DickGregory.htm |title=Dick Gregory, For the People |publisher=africanamericans.com |accessdate=2007-07-06}}</ref> }} {{mem/f |name=George Haynes |chapter="unknown" |nota=First President of the [[National Urban League]]; First African American to receive a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] from [[Columbia University]] |ref=<ref name=nul>{{cite web |url=http://www.nul.org/history.html |title=History of the National Urban League |publisher=nul.org |accessdate=2007-07-14 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070707181451/http://www.nul.org/history.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-07-07}}</ref>}} {{mem/f |name=[[John Hope (educator)|John Hope]]<!-- Also in "Academia" 